  <div class="container">
    <h2 class="section-title">Context</h2>
    <div class="case-study-prose">
      <p>
        The consulting work here spans consumer real estate, enterprise fintech, and behavioral
        health — three industries with different users, different stakes, and very different
        definitions of success. What held across all of them: the fastest path to the right
        answer is talking to customers before you build anything.
      </p>
      <p>
        Each engagement sharpened a different edge. Realtor.com was about proving that
        transparency could outperform deception at scale. Capital One was about redirecting
        a build that was already in motion. Healify was about building something from scratch,
        watching it fail, and understanding why deeply enough to rebuild it correctly.
      </p>
      <p>
        Taken together, they represent the core of how I work: research first, build lean,
        measure what matters, and don't protect the wrong ideas.
      </p>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

